name: Set
description: Represents a collection of unique elements with no duplicate values.

add(object).name: add
add(object).description: Adds an element to the set if it is not already present.

addall(list<object>).name: addAll
addall(list<object>).description: Adds all of the elements in the specified list to the set if they are not already present.

addall(set<object>).name: addAll
addall(set<object>).description: Adds all of the elements in the specified set to the set that calls the method if they are not already present.

clear().name: clear
clear().description: Removes all of the elements from the set.

clone().name: clone
clone().description: Makes a duplicate copy of the set.

contains(object).name: contains
contains(object).description: Returns true if the set contains the specified element.

containsall(list<object>).name: containsAll
containsall(list<object>).description: Returns true if the set contains all of the elements in the specified list. The list must be of the same type as the set that calls the method.

containsall(set<object>).name: containsAll
containsall(set<object>).description: Returns true if the set contains all of the elements in the specified set. The specified set must be of the same type as the original set that calls the method.

equals(set<object>).name: equals
equals(set<object>).description: Compares this set with the specified set and returns true if both sets are equal; otherwise, returns false.

set2.name: set2
set2.description: The set2 argument is the set to compare this set with.

hashcode().name: hashCode
hashcode().description: Returns the hashcode corresponding to this set and its contents.

isempty().name: isEmpty
isempty().description: Returns true if the set has zero elements.

remove(object).name: remove
remove(object).description: Removes the specified element from the set if it is present.

removeall(list<object>).name: removeAll
removeall(list<object>).description: Removes the elements in the specified list from the set if they are present.

removeall(set<object>).name: removeAll
removeall(set<object>).description: Removes the elements in the specified set from the original set if they are present.

retainall(list<object>).name: retainAll
retainall(list<object>).description: Retains only the elements in this set that are contained in the specified list.

retainall(set).name: retainAll
retainall(set).description: Retains only the elements in the original set that are contained in the specified set.

size().name: size
size().description: Returns the number of elements in the set (its cardinality).

set&lt;t&gt;().name: Set<T>
set&lt;t&gt;().description: Creates a new instance of the Set class. A set can hold elements of any data type T.

set&lt;t&gt;(set<t>).name: Set<T>
set&lt;t&gt;(set<t>).description: Creates a new instance of the Set class by copying the elements of the specified set. T is the data type of the elements in both sets and can be any data type.

settocopy.name: setToCopy
settocopy.description: The set to initialize this set with.

set&lt;t&gt;(list<t>).name: Set<T>
set&lt;t&gt;(list<t>).description: Creates a new instance of the Set class by coping the list elements. T is the data type of the elements in the set and list and can be any data type.

listtocopy.name: listToCopy
listtocopy.description: The list to copy the elements of into this set.
